Hei everyone! I've setup a webhook and created the necessary subscriptions on my public app. I created an endpoint on my nodejs server to handle it and I receive the information on every contact update. But I can't get the hash in the header to be validated against the client secret of my public app.
I got the client secret from my developer account/Apps/my_app/Auth/Client secret
This is how my logic looks like
```import {Request, Response, NextFunction} from 'express'
import {IncomingMessage} from 'http'
import crypto from 'crypto'
interface RawBodyVerifyType extends Partial&lt;Request&gt; {
  rawBody?:string
}

const generateSHA256Hash = (value:string) =&gt; {
  const hash = crypto.createHash('sha256')
  hash.update(value)
  return hash.digest('hex')
}

export const HubSpotWebhook = async (req:RawBodyVerifyType, res:Response, next:NextFunction) =&gt; {
  const requestSignature = process.env.HubSpot_CLIENT_SECRET' + req.body
  const hashRequestSignature = generateSHA256Hash(requestSignature)
  const HubSpotSignature = req.headers?.['x-HubSpot-signature']

  if (hashRequestSignature !== HubSpotSignature) {
    console.log('Invalid Signature')
    res.status(200).send({ok: false})
    return
  }
  console.log('Valid Signature')
  res.status(200).send({ok: true})
}```
hashRequestSignature !== HubSpotSignature is always true, even when I paste the client secret directly in the code instead of using dotenv.
Do you see anything wrong with this logic? I would appreciate any help that could point me in the right direction please. Thanks
